        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3470432686" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12178806728376101683">The esteemed author, will forgive me, but I found it to be a hard, solemn, disparaging read. This book is very touching though somewhat depressing throughout, with various similarities to Beloved by Toni Morrison and The handmaid&apos;s tale by Margaret Atwood. It addresses numerous topics of injustice varying from discrimination based on sex, gender, class, race, social standing to oppression, rape and various additional social norms that are composed to become the predominant elements of this body </span>
  <span id="freeText12178806728376101683" style="display:none">The esteemed author, will forgive me, but I found it to be a hard, solemn, disparaging read. This book is very touching though somewhat depressing throughout, with various similarities to Beloved by Toni Morrison and The handmaid's tale by Margaret Atwood. It addresses numerous topics of injustice varying from discrimination based on sex, gender, class, race, social standing to oppression, rape and various additional social norms that are composed to become the predominant elements of this body of work. It is done quite masterfully, burdening the reader with plenty to reflect and experience emotions of empathy, sympathy, guilt, fear, anger and remorse to write a few. At times, the bleeding heart may be considered quite a flowing gush, if only we could say that none of had actually happened in some form and time throughout human history.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12178806728376101683" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


