    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4215033786" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4215033786" />
    <a title="Lars Yencken" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18821077-lars-yencken"><img alt="Lars Yencken" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1628235970p2/18821077.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4215033786?book_show_action=true">Sep 05, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lars Yencken" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lars Yencken" href="/user/show/18821077-lars-yencken">Lars Yencken</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4215033786" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4214396135806709385">I drank in this book like I drink in all of Ursula Le Guin&apos;s work. The characters she builds feel like rich human beings, always.<br/><br/>This book is like several interwoven novellas. Each of them is nearly standalone, but they overlap substantially, so that a main character in one is a fringe character in another. Each of Le Guin&apos;s Hainish cycle novels seems to tackle one big area. The biggest themes of Four Ways to Forgiveness are slavery, freedom and women&apos;s emancipation.</span>
  <span id="freeText4214396135806709385" style="display:none">I drank in this book like I drink in all of Ursula Le Guin's work. The characters she builds feel like rich human beings, always.<br /><br />This book is like several interwoven novellas. Each of them is nearly standalone, but they overlap substantially, so that a main character in one is a fringe character in another. Each of Le Guin's Hainish cycle novels seems to tackle one big area. The biggest themes of Four Ways to Forgiveness are slavery, freedom and women's emancipation.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4214396135806709385" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


